quran[29]{c,v,t}:
  27,27,"Solomon said, \"We shall soon see whether you have spoken the truth, or whether you are a liar"
  27,28,"Go with this letter of mine and lay it before them, then withdraw from them and see how they respond"
  27,29,"The Queen of Sheba said, \"O Counsellors, an honourable letter has been delivered to me"
  27,30,"It is from Solomon. It reads, \"In the name of God, Most Gracious, Most Merciful"
  27,31,"do not exalt yourselves above me, but come to me in all submission"
  27,32,"Now advise me in this, Counsellors. I never decide any affair till I have conferred with you"
  27,33,"They said, \"We are strong and our prowess in battle is great, but the decision is in your hands, so consider what you will command"
  27,34,"She said, \"Surely, when mighty kings invade a country, they despoil it and humiliate its noblest inhabitants, these men will do the same"
  27,35,but I shall send them a present and see with what reply my envoys will return
  27,36,"So when [the envoy] came to Solomon he said, \"What! Are you offering me wealth? But that which God has given me is better than that which He has given you. Yet you rejoice in your gift"
  27,37,"Go back to them: we shall most certainly come upon them with forces which they will never be able to withstand, and shall most certainly cause them to be driven from their lands, disgraced and humbled"
  27,38,"Solomon then said, \"O Counsellors, which of you can bring me her throne before they come to me in submission"
  27,39,"A demon from among the jinn said, \"I will bring it to you before you get up from your seat. I am strong and trustworthy enough to do it"
  27,40,"But one of them who had some knowledge of the Book said, \"I will bring it to you in the twinkling of an eye.\" When Solomon saw it placed before him, he exclaimed, \"This is by the grace of my Lord, to test whether I am grateful or ungrateful. Whosoever is grateful, it is for the good of his own self; and whosoever is ungrateful, then surely my Lord is self-sufficient and generous"
  27,41,"He said, \"Disguise her throne. We shall see whether or not she will recognize it"
  27,42,"When she came to Solomon, she was asked, \"Is your throne like this?\" She replied, \"It looks as though it were the same, and we had been given knowledge [of your power] before this, and we have already submitted"
  27,43,"And that which she used to worship beside God had stopped her [from believing]; for she came of a disbelieving people"
  27,44,"Then she was bidden to enter the palace; but when she saw it, she thought it was a deep pool of water, and bared her legs. But Solomon explained, \"It is just a palace paved with glass,\" and she said, \"My Lord, I have wronged myself: now I submit myself along with Solomon, to God, the Lord of the Universe"
  27,45,"To Thamud We sent their brother Salih. He said, \"Serve none but God.\" But they divided themselves into two factions contending with one another"
  27,46,"He urged them, \"O my people, why do you wish to hasten on the evil rather than the good? Why do you not ask forgiveness of God, so that you may be shown mercy"
  27,47,"They said, \"We see you and your followers as an evil omen.\" He replied, \"No, your evil omen is with God; the truth is that you are a people being put to the test"
  27,48,"There were in the city nine men who spread corruption in the land, and would not reform"
  27,49,"They said, \"Let us bind ourselves by an oath sworn in the name of God that we shall attack Salih and his family by night, and to his protector [who demands retribution], we shall say, \"We were not present when they were slain. We are telling the truth"
  27,50,"Thus they devised a plan, and We also devised a plan, but they were not aware of it"
  27,51,"See, then, what the consequences of their plan were. We destroyed them and their people utterly, all together"
  27,52,"Because of their wrongdoing, their houses are in ruins, in that surely there is a sign for people who have knowledge"
  27,53,and We saved those who believed in and feared God
  27,54,"And tell of Lot. He said to his people, \"Will you commit evil knowingly"
  27,55,"Must you go lustfully to men instead of women? Indeed, you are a people who are deeply ignorant"